Kenya has confirmed 106 more cases of the novel coronavirus from a sample of 3,315 tested in the last 24 hours.
In a statement to media houses on Monday, the Ministry of Health said the new infections pushed the total number of declared cases in the country to 96,908.
Thus far, Kenya has analysed 1,059,006 samples for Covid-19, which was first confirmed in the country on March 13, 2020. The virus was first detected in Wuhan, China, on December 31, 2019.



