Of the 106 patients, 97 were Kenyans and the rest foreigners, 77 male, 29 female, the youngest nine and the oldest 70.
Health Cabinet Secretary Mutahi Kagwe further reported the recovery of 184 more patients, 131 from the home-based care programme while 53 from various hospitals, raising the total to 79,257.
In the last 24 hours, one patient succumbed to the virus, bringing the number of fatalities to 1,686.



