Admissions
The ministry further said that by Monday, 617 patients had been admitted in health facilities countywide while 2,964 were being treated at home.
Twenty eight of them were in intensive care unit (ICU), 13 on ventilatory support, 12 on supplemental oxygen and three under observation.
Another 19 patients were on supplemental oxygen but in general wards.
Nairobi accounted for 87 of the new cases, Uasin Gishu five, Kiambu three, Busia, Kajiado and Mombasa two each, and Machakos, Makueni, Kericho, Meru and Kilifi one each. The AstraZeneca vaccine is the only hope for Kenyans since it is cheaper and easier to store and distribute compared to the others. Learning institutions were shut in March to contain the spread of the coronavirus. Pope Francis has accepted his resignation, which came after he attained the mandatory retirement age. Nyeri Town MP Mr Ngunjiri Wambugu said Mr Kang’ata was not sincere in his letter for sharing it with the media and the public. Learning institutions were shut in March to contain the spread of the coronavirus.